This paper deals with optimization of wireless networks with Age of Information (AoI) constraints, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses Lyapunov optimization theory, which is a tool commonly used in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper formulates a stochastic optimization problem, which falls under the category of mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper studies the performance of the proposed algorithm through simulation results, which is a common practice in game theory (cs.GT).
